public abstract class VdrSearchTerm
extends Object
implements Cloneable

The VdrSearchTerm abstract class is the base class of search terms used by the VdrSearchExpression class. A VdrSearchTerm is either a search constraint OR a VdrSearchExpression sub-expression.

A Search Constraint is comprised of:

  • An Attribute or Field
  • A comparison operator, such as ComparisonOperators.EQ
  • A Comparison value or value array (to support operators that require left and right values, such as Between)
A sub-expression contains search terms and is used to create complex search expression trees.

The concrete search term classes are:

  • ReportSearchTerm
  • VersionSearchTerm
  • SectionSearchTerm
  • TopicSearchTerm
  • SubExpressionSearchTerm
